description: Number of distinct anagrams of digits of n without leading zeros.
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: a(101)=2 since the digits of 101 can be ordered 101 or 110 (but not 011)
mathematica: a[n_] := Length[ DeleteCases[ Permutations[ IntegerDigits[n]], {0 .., __}]]; Table[a[n], {n, 1, 102}] (* _Jean-FranÃ§ois Alcover_, Nov 30 2011 *)
prog: (Haskell)import Data.List (permutations, nub)a055098 n = length $ nub $ filter ((> '0') . head) $ permutations $ show n-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 14 2011
